{"id":"project-LICHEN-dz63","title":"Lost error code in enqueue_static_sync error handling","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshtastic/adapter.c:1339-1392

Multiple instances of this pattern:
  ret = lichen_meshtastic_encode_my_info_payload(info, payload, sizeof(payload));
  if (ret < 0 || enqueue_payload(adapter, ..., payload, (size_t)ret) < 0) {
      return ret < 0 ? ret : -ENOMEM;
  }

When encode succeeds (ret >= 0) but enqueue_payload fails, the actual error from enqueue_payload is discarded and replaced with -ENOMEM.

This loses diagnostic information. For example, if enqueue_payload returned -ENOTCONN, the caller sees -ENOMEM instead.

Fix: Capture enqueue_payload return value:
  int enqueue_ret = enqueue_payload(...);
  if (ret < 0 || enqueue_ret < 0) {
      return ret < 0 ? ret : enqueue_ret;
  }","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:48:20.83019Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:48:20.830231Z"}
